</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uvalaelvalacirca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valael Valacirca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ks.gamerzparadize.com/smileys/gunless%20violence/312.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1019<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(2/27/02 12:03:26 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ks.gamerzparadize.com/smileys/gunless%20violence/bangin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poll:    How has DAoC affected EQ for you??</span><hr size=1> I take back everything I said about DAoC.<br>
<br>
<br>
It's a great game....*ONLY* if you take your time.<br>
<br>
<br>
The high end game is boring as can be.  The uber zones they added are well..boring.  I found EQ's to be more entertaining.  Maybe it was just the addiction speaking, maybe it was something else.<br>
<br>
As for AO - I'd rate it above DAoC in it's current state.<br>
<br>
<br>
AO only has missions, pvp, and the leveling thing.  I'd still say it has more content than DAoC (Well, not really, but it's certainly more entertaining)<br>
<br>
<br>
Like someone else said:  You *CAN'T* explore.  The world is simply too small.  MAYBE frontiers, but well...what do you expect to see?  There aren't many unique things in DAoC's world other than mobs.  The reason why? (Atleast this is my theory) Lack of zoning.  You might hate it, but once you play in a world with NO zoning and a landscape as dull as DAoC's, you'll grow to apprecaite the uniqueness the zones in EQ or AO have.<br>
<br>
<br>
As for Horizon's - Check out the offical page.  The game is vaporware - they don't even HAVE an offical page anymore.  I highly doubt it'll be coming out.  Who knows though, maybe it'll rise from the dead.<br>
<br>
<br>
As for me, my next big MMORPG is going to be Earth and Beyond.  After getting accepted to the Phase 6 stress test and reading up on it, I can't wait for it to start.  (Note:  That doesn't mean it's a good game, I just mean that if they give half the things they say, it'll be a great game....but not many MMORPGs pull that off..they usually leave a few things out.)<br>
<br>
But one think struck me as interesting: Leveling.  Three types of exp you can do (You can't max out all three though).  You get exp for trading, exploring, and killing.  Currently, you can explore and put points into killing skills.  I kinda doubt it'll stay that way.  (Note:  This is just stuff I've read.  I could be off base, but after playing a few MMORPGs, I kinda see that being a little too easy)<br>
<br>
<br>
After Earth and Beyond, maybe I'll try out Eve, a much less known MMORPG coming out, but by far the best looking (I don't know much about it other than that though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
And..of course..WoW.. Gotta try anything Blizzard makes.  I'm such a fan boy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Yeah..I guess I planned out my MMORPG future. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=karakas>Karakas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(3/4/02 11:29:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poll:    How has DAoC affected EQ for you??</span><hr size=1> I left EQ alot.  And I always return.  No matter what they do to me.  DAoC was great, but no where near as big as EQ.  I came back recently to start my monk.  Couldn't bear to play another Necro ( mine was slain by VI nerf stick. Glad to see they put it away.  Well.. at least for now.) I did like the fact that n00b quests and armor were attainable in DAoC. I think this is something EQ always lacked.  No love for non-twinks.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uvalaelvalacirca.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valael Valacirca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ks.gamerzparadize.com/smileys/gunless%20violence/312.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1050<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(3/7/02 5:32:35 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ks.gamerzparadize.com/smileys/gunless%20violence/bangin.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poll:    How has DAoC affected EQ for you??</span><hr size=1> I kinda agree.<br>
